721253f.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 30th Street (East)
721253f.text:
Madison Ave., west side, north from East 30th (left) to 31st Streets,
showing prominently the Carroll House, No. 122 Madison Ave., that was
built in 1907, as the Colony Club. For an article on same see the
New York Times of February 17, 1907, Sunday Magazine Section, Part 3.
January 30, 1938.
George D. Chinn.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

730238f-a.title: General view - [Manhattan - 30th Street - Madison Avenue (Northwest).]
730238f-a.text:
A general view, northwest from the N.E. corner of 30th Street and
Madison Ave., showing the Empire State Building nearing completion.
August 2, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

721263f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 30th Street (East)
721263f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, west side, south from 33rd Street, showing the
Remsen and Backer buildingE, just completed, between 32nd and
31st Streets. Between 31st and 30th Streets may be seen the
front of the old Colony Club building, which will be demolished
about 1918.
